mond joined in 2012. Sharing how officials cautiously and often unwittingly allowed the newspaper to tell the stories of the incarcerated, Prison Truth illustrates the power of prison media to humanize the experiences of people inside penitentiary walls and to forge alliances with social justice networks seeking reform.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 0aPrison newspaperszCaliforniazSan Quentin. 0aPrisoners as journalistszCaliforniazSan Quentin. 0aPrisonerszCaliforniazSan QuentinxSocial conditions. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Criminology.2bisacsh  a2008.  aamerica.  aarnulfo garcia.  abastille by the bay.  acalifornia.  adangerous prisoners.  aenlightened warden.  afostering positive changes.  ahumanizing criminals.  aincarcerated stories.  ainmates.  ajohnny cash.  alife terms.  aliving hell.  anewspaper.  aprison climate.  aprison reform.  aprisoners.  aprisons.  arehabilitation.  aretired newspaper veterans.  asan quentin news.  asan quentin state prison.  asocial justice networks.  aunited states.  avisionary prisoner.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2020 Englishz978311070472308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology, Education, Psychology 2020z9783110704549oZDB-23-SEW08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press Frontlist eBook-Package 2020z978311069041540uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520970526zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520970526423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780520970526.jpg  a978-3-11-069